# No dict in function signatures

**Rule:** No `dict`, `Dict`, or `TypedDict` in function parameters or return types.

**Use instead:**
- Pydantic `BaseModel` for structured data
- `RootModel[dict[str, X]]` for JSON-RPC–style payloads

**Exception:** Third-party callbacks that require dict in/out (e.g. ASGI, monkey-patches)—add `# no-dict-sig` and a short comment explaining the exception.

**Enforcement:** `make check-no-dict-sig` and ruff `banned-api`; CI fails on violations.

See [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) and [types-and-pydantic.md](../../docs/reference/types-and-pydantic.md).
